Commentary Text: Boult to Gowtham, out Lbw!! Plumb. And Lucknow's experiment of sending Gowtham as some sort of a nightwatchman falls flat. This one's an inswinging ripper as well, from over the wicket for a change, drifting across at first, pitching well outside off, and straightening back in to pin him in front of middle-stump. Quinton doesn't even bother with the review discussion. Gowtham lbw b Boult 0(1)

Commentary Text: Boult to Rahul, out Bowled!! A ripper of an inswinging jaffa. It's a rocket. A bolt. A peach. It's full, tailing back in, Rahul plays all around it, looking to flick it into the leg-side, but falling over and Boult's round the wicket angle goes through bat and pad to uproot both off and middle stump. Rahul b Boult 0(1)
